The Lagos State governor, Mr Babajide Olushola Sanwo-Olu, on Tuesday approved the reconstitution of Boards of the State Employment Trust Fund (LSETF) and the State Security Trust Fund (LSSTF). Gov Sanwo-Olu, in a statement yesterday signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr Gboyega Akosile, explained that the new board appointments, which took immediate effect, were necessitated by the vacancies in the two organizations. According to him, the new members were carefully chosen based on records of excellence in their chosen fields. While the governor thanked the previous members of the two Boards for their meritorious and conscientious service to the state, he congratulated and thanked the new members for accepting to serve the state and help improve on the achievements of their predecessors. Dear our valued reader, we would like to hear your view about a membership club that we plan to launch. Kindly help us fill this survey. The new eight-man Board for the LSETF is headed by Mrs Bola Adesola as chairman, while Mrs Abisoye Tejumola is the Executive Secretary. Also, the new 12-man LSSTF board is chaired by Mr Kehinde Durosinmi-Etti, while Dr Abdul Razaq Balogun is the Executive Secretary. 1,300 youths, women acquire vocational skills Ambode inaugurates LSSTF board Sanwo-Olu swears-in permanent secretaries, inaugurates committees